{"title_page": "Memons (Kathiawar)", "text_new": "{{Refimprove|date=January 2011}}\nThe ancestors of present-day [[Memon people|Memons]] who settled a few centuries ago in various parts of Gujarat State in India, This region of India was known as [[Kathiawar]]. Currently this region is known as [[Saurashtra (region)|Saurashtra]].  \n\n'''[[Memon people|Memon]]''' people that originated in Kathiawar region are known as [[Kathiawar|Kathiawari Memons]]. Memons are identified through their ancestral villages or by their Memon surnames (Jaat) within their respective Memon community. Kathiawari memons trace their lineage to towns or villages in modern-day Gujarat state, India. These villages are such as '''[[Kutiyana]], [[Bantva]],''' '''[[Porbandar]],''' '''[[Ranavav]]''', [https://www.google.com/search?ei=BCIWXt-vLoyE4-EPvP-MyA8&q=vadasada+village+gujarat&oq=vadasada&gs_l=psy-ab.3.2.0l3j0i30l2j0i5i30l3.74595.75746..77440...0.0..0.445.961.2-2j0j1......0....1..gws-wiz.UmSKj-fhq8w '''Vadasada'''], '''[[Kodinar]], [[Dhoraji]], [[Jamnagar]], [[Jetpur, Navagadh|Jetpur]], [[Gondal, India|Gondal]], [[Manavadar]], [[Okha, India|Okhai]], [[Upleta]], [[Vanthali]], [[Veraval|Veraval]], [[Rajkot]]'''. \n\nKathiawari Memons are further divided into sub-group.  This is generally through their ancestral village or town and surname. Memon people are identified as Kutiyana Memons, Porbandar Memons, [[Bantva|Bantva Memons]], [[Dhoraji|Dhoraji Memons]], Upleta memons or generally known as [[Kathiawar|Kathiawari memons]] among the international memon community. There are Memon people that traces their villages based in the [[Kutch district|Kutch]] region of modern India. Memon people from [[Kutch district|Kutch region]] are known as Kutchi memons; They speak the [[Kutchi language]] and follow the [[Hanafi|Sunni Hanafi Islam]].\n\nKathiawari Memon people are often considered the typical Memon ethnic group; that widely migrated and settled around the world in countries like [[Memon people|Pakistan]], [[Memons in Sri Lanka|Sri Lanka]], [[Memons in South Africa|South Africa]], [[Memon people|Kenya]], Malawi, Mauritius, Botswana, Tanzania, [[Memon people|The United Kingdom]], [[Memon people|The United States and Canada]]. The language of Kathiawari Memons is called [[Memon language|Memoni Language]]. Memoni Language shares vocabularies of [[Kutchi language]], [[Gujarati language|Gujarati Language]] and [[Sindhi language|Sindhi Language]].\n\n== Khathiawar Memon Surnames (Jaath) ==\nMemon Surnames or Jaat, is a title that is inherited by male members of the Memon family through their Paternal ancestors. This caste system is widely distributed among other ethnic groups in India and other parts of the [[Indian subcontinent|Indian Subcontinent]]. The Memon surname or Jaat is given high importance, due to verification and to point out the reliability of the Memon family in a community. Memon surnames were inherited though generations to identify the status and profession of the Memon family in its respective [[Jama'at Khana|jamaath khana]]. Most Popular Kathiawari Memon Surnames are as follows:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!'''Admani'''\n!Adamjee\n!'''Bandhani'''\n!'''Bagha'''\n!Batviya\n!Bandhukra\n!Bharda\n!'''Bhukan'''\n!'''Bhailla'''\n!'''Bhiriya'''\n!'''Bhuri'''\n!Bhutta\n!Bhungra\n!'''Budhani'''\n!'''Bhoja'''\n|-\n!'''Dada'''\n!Dhaga\n!'''Darvesh'''\n!'''Dangra'''\n!Dadia\n!Dhedhi\n!'''Dewan'''\n!'''Dosani'''\n!'''Fathani'''\n!'''Fullara'''\n!'''Gaba'''\n!Gadar\n!Gabrani\n!Gandhi\n!Gani\n|-\n!Hingora\n!Jangda\n!Janoo\n!'''Jandoola'''\n!Jamku\n!Katkodia\n!Kutchi\n!'''Kaba'''\n!'''Kaludi'''\n!'''Kapadia'''\n!'''Khatliya'''\n!Kandhoi\n!Khaku\n!'''Khiyani'''\n!Lakhani\n|-\n!'''Maghoora'''\n!Masidiya\n!'''Mayari'''\n!'''Mengrani'''\n!Jardhi\n!Noorani\n!'''Nagariya'''\n!'''Odedara'''\n!'''Pochi'''\n!'''Panjwani'''\n!'''Patel'''\n!Padiyar\n!Parekh\n!'''Rah'''\n!'''Rahila'''\n|-\n!'''Rangila'''\n!Sacranie\n!'''Sangani'''\n!'''Sayani'''\n!Surti\n!Sutarviya\n!'''Silat'''\n!'''Somar'''\n!'''Sikiladha'''\n!Suriya\n!Sait\n!Tai\n!Thar\n!'''Varindh'''\n!'''Vindhani'''\n|-\n!Vayani\n!Gadith\n!Godil\n!Shivani\n!Mandhai\n!Mundiya\n!Helabeli\n!Chamadia\n!Vadasada\n!Ranavaya\n!Manchala\n!Hadfa\n!Channa\n!Okhai\n!Zolkha\n|}\n\n\n<nowiki>***</nowiki>The above [[Memon people|Memon]] surnames are largely inherited by [[Memon people|Memons]] that trace back their lineage to [[Kutiyana]] and [[Bantva]] village in [[Gujarat|Gujarat State, India]]***\n\n==See also==\n*[[Memon people|Memon People]]\n*[[Memoni language|Memoni Language]]\n*[[Kutchi language|Kuthci Language]]\n*[[Sindhi language|Sindhi Language]] \n*[[Saurashtra (region)|Kathiawar (Saurashtra)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Social groups of Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Memon| ]]\n[[Category:Muslim communities of Gujarat]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=January 2011}}\nThe ancestors of present-day [[Memon people|Memons]] who settled a few centuries ago in various parts of Gujarat State in India, This region of India was known as [[Kathiawar]]. Currently this region is known as [[Saurashtra (region)|Saurashtra]].  \n\n'''[[Memon people|Memon]]''' people that originated in Kathiawar region are known as [[Kathiawar|Kathiawari Memons]]. Memons are identified through their ancestral villages or by their Memon surnames (Jaat) within their respective Memon community. Kathiawari memons trace their lineage to towns or villages in modern-day Gujarat state, India. These villages are such as '''[[Kutiyana]], [[Bantva]],''' '''[[Porbandar]],''' '''[[Ranavav]]''', [https://www.google.com/search?ei=BCIWXt-vLoyE4-EPvP-MyA8&q=vadasada+village+gujarat&oq=vadasada&gs_l=psy-ab.3.2.0l3j0i30l2j0i5i30l3.74595.75746..77440...0.0..0.445.961.2-2j0j1......0....1..gws-wiz.UmSKj-fhq8w '''Vadasada'''], '''[[Kodinar]], [[Dhoraji]], [[Jamnagar]], [[Jetpur, Navagadh|Jetpur]], [[Gondal, India|Gondal]], [[Manavadar]], [[Okha, India|Okhai]], [[Upleta]], [[Vanthali]], [[Veraval|Veraval]], [[Rajkot]]'''. \n\nKathiawari Memons are further divided into sub-group.  This is generally through their ancestral village or town and surname. Memon people are identified as Kutiyana Memons, Porbandar Memons, [[Bantva|Bantva Memons]], [[Dhoraji|Dhoraji Memons]], Upleta memons or generally known as [[Kathiawar|Kathiawari memons]] among the international memon community. There are Memon people that traces their villages based in the [[Kutch district|Kutch]] region of modern India. Memon people from [[Kutch district|Kutch region]] are known as Kutchi memons; They speak the [[Kutchi language]] and follow the [[Hanafi|Sunni Hanafi Islam]].\n\nKathiawari Memon people are often considered the typical Memon ethnic group; that widely migrated and settled around the world in countries like [[Memon people|Pakistan]], [[Memons in Sri Lanka|Sri Lanka]], [[Memons in South Africa|South Africa]], [[Memon people|Kenya]], Malawi, Mauritius, Botswana, Tanzania, [[Memon people|The United Kingdom]], [[Memon people|The United States and Canada]]. The language of Kathiawari Memons is called [[Memon language|Memoni Language]]. Memoni Language shares vocabularies of [[Kutchi language]], [[Gujarati language|Gujarati Language]] and [[Sindhi language|Sindhi Language]].\n\n== Khathiawar Memon Surnames (Jaath) ==\nMemon Surnames or Jaat, is a title that is inherited by male members of the Memon family through their Paternal ancestors. This caste system is widely distributed among other ethnic groups in India and other parts of the [[Indian subcontinent|Indian Subcontinent]]. The Memon surname or Jaat is given high importance, due to verification and to point out the reliability of the Memon family in a community. Memon surnames were inherited though generations to identify the status and profession of the Memon family in its respective [[Jama'at Khana|jamaath khana]]. Most Popular Kathiawari Memon Surnames are as follows:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!'''Admani'''\n!Adamjee\n!'''Bandhani'''\n!'''Bagha'''\n